On Wednesday, April 04, 2012 10:24 PM, Mike Kelly wrote:
&gt; 
&gt; All of it that has nothing to do with representing links to, and
&gt; containment of, other resources.. which is quite a lot?

Linking to other resources:

{
  &quot;@context&quot;: &quot;/context.jsonld&quot;,
  &quot;@id&quot;: &quot;http://example.com/markus&quot;,
  &quot;name&quot;: &quot;Markus Lanthaler&quot;,
  &quot;knows&quot;: &quot;http://example.com/mike&quot;
}


Embedding resources:

{
  &quot;@context&quot;: &quot;/context.jsonld&quot;,
  &quot;@id&quot;: &quot;http://example.com/markus&quot;,
  &quot;name&quot;: &quot;Markus Lanthaler&quot;,
  &quot;knows&quot;: {
    &quot;@id&quot;: &quot;http://example.com/mike&quot;,
    &quot;name&quot;: &quot;Mike Kelly&quot;
  }
}


All you have to do is to define your context once, and store it somewhere:

&quot;@context&quot;: {
    &quot;foaf: &quot;http://...&quot;,
    &quot;name&quot;: &quot;foaf:name&quot;,
    &quot;knows&quot;: { &quot;foaf:knows&quot;, &quot;@type&quot;: &quot;@id&quot; }
}


Too complex?



